{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0145pQH3xhh5KSLjmNFcv4FC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01766UZw7EXwsiP9vvqVYq3j","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/markus/baustelle/projects/agents-in-the-office/agents-in-the-office/.chief/prds/sound-packs-patchbay/progress.md","content":"## Codebase Patterns\n- `soundStore.ts` is the single source of truth for audio config; all Vue components read from `soundStore.config`\n- `getTrackConfig(packName, categoryAndFile)` accepts legacy \"category/filename\" key format; extracts filename internally\n- `soundOverrides` uses flat key `\"packName/filename\"` — NOT nested by pack like the old `tracks` field\n- When renaming a pack, iterate `soundOverrides` keys to move `oldName/file` → `newName/file`\n- When deleting a pack, filter `soundOverrides` keys by `startsWith(\"packName/\")` prefix\n- Vue components directly mutate `soundStore.config.*` reactively — this is intentional (Pinia reactive state)\n- `bun run build` runs `vue-tsc -b && vite build` — use this to verify type correctness\n- TypeScript `@deprecated` JSDoc on interface fields generates `ts(6385)` warnings; avoid it, use plain comments instead\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-04 - US-002\n- What was implemented:\n  - Added `soundOverrides: Record<string, { volume: number; enabled: boolean }>` to `SoundConfig` (key: `packName/filename`)\n  - Made `tracks` optional in `SoundConfig` with migration support\n  - Added `migrateTracksToSoundOverrides()` pure function: extracts filename from old `category/filename` key\n  - Updated `init()` to migrate legacy `tracks` → `soundOverrides` on read, then drops `tracks` from in-memory config\n  - Rewrote `getTrackConfig`/`setTrackConfig` to use `soundOverrides` internally (still accept legacy `category/filename` keys)\n  - Added `effectiveVolume(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` and `isEnabled(packName, filename, manifestSound?)` two-layer helpers\n  - Updated `PackContextMenu.vue`: rename migrates `soundOverrides` keys, delete removes all keys for pack\n  - Updated `SoundsDialog.vue`: delete track removes from `soundOverrides` by `packName/filename` key\n- Files changed:\n  - `src/stores/soundStore.ts`\n  - `src/components/PackContextMenu.vue`\n  - `src/components/SoundsDialog.vue`\n- **Learnings for future iterations:**\n  - The old `tracks` field was nested `tracks[packName][categoryAndFile]`; the new `soundOverrides` is flat `soundOverrides[\"packName/filename\"]`\n  - `@deprecated` JSDoc triggers `ts(6385)` which counts as a warning — use plain comments instead\n  - Multiple Vue components accessed `soundStore.config.tracks` directly — always grep for usages across all components when changing a config field\n---\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":269,"cache_read_input_tokens":69013,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":269},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b273f168-5152-4d5e-b9e2-1d2ad43401b5","uuid":"10210067-6fdb-4567-b2da-8ac4d88b32f3"}
