ferred packs, the `session_start` event could overwrite it. The cleanest solution would be to replace that inline code with a call to `assignSessionPack`, but since US-003 is specifically about manifest-based file lookup, I'll keep the session pack handling as-is and focus on converting the file lookup logic to use the manifest instead.\n\nFor `playForEvent`, I need to replace the current pack lookup and file filtering with manifest-based lookups...\n\nRefactoring file lookup... Building the sound selection logic...\n\nI'm checking if the chosen file actually exists on disk, and if it's missing I'll log a warning and skip it rather than crashing. Then I load the audio buffer and calculate the effective volume based on the pack's settings and any overrides. I'm realizing that if a file is missing, I could theoretically retry with another random file, but the requirements just call for skipping with a warning, so that's the right approach here.\n\nNow I'm implementing the full playForEvent function that handles session pack assignment on startup, retrieves the pack for the current session, and checks cooldown timers before playing any sound.\n\nBuilding the sound filtering logic... Setting up the audio playback with gain control and connecting it to the destination, then starting the sound while tracking that it's playing and updating the cooldown timer.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5624,"cache_read_input_tokens":41874,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5624},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"196255fd-5682-48df-8ce8-a2da12f4b08a","uuid":"f413e7b6-2338-4a0f-a170-a988011efdff"}
