o scroll the right panel back to the top.\n\nThen I'm creating a function to check which sound files actually exist in the file system by mapping through the manifest and testing each one. Finally, I'm adding a cleanup function that stops any currently playing preview audio, with error handling in case the source is already stopped.\n\nSetting up audio playback... Writing component template... Writing the sound list component... Writing component markup... I'm settling on a per-row implementation where each sound has its own play and stop buttons always visible, with the stop button only functional when that specific sound is playing. I need to add the `exists` function to the Tauri fs imports and import the `PackManifestSound` type, then write out the updated component.\n\nWriting the component... Still writing the watch handler... fire before scanPacks() completes, so leaving immediate as false is the right call. When selectedPack gets set in onMounted, the watch will trigger and selectedPackInfo will already be populated from the completed scan, so checkSoundFileExistence will have the manifest sounds to work with. Now I'm thinking through the overall structure—I need previewSource as a non-reactive variable to hold the AudioBufferSourceNode, but I'm realizing there might be an issue when I call stopPreview() in the watch before checking the new pack's sounds, since selectedPackInfo depends on selectedPack which is being updated to the new value. That should actually work fine though—selectedPackInfo will reflect the new pack's manifest. Let me start writing out the edits.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12512,"cache_read_input_tokens":42901,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12512},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eae6a30b-1237-4ce